{"doc":{"isMarkdown":false,"isTranslated":true,"isActive":false,"flaws":{},"title":"Geolocation","mdn_url":"/de/docs/Web/API/Geolocation","locale":"de","native":"Deutsch","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/API/Geolocation_API\">Geolocation API</a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/API/Geolocation\"><code>Geolocation</code></a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Methoden</summary><ol><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Geolocation/clearWatch\"><code>clearWatch()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/API/Geolocation/getCurrentPosition\"><code>getCurrentPosition()</code></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Geolocation/watchPosition\"><code>watchPosition()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Ähnliche Seiten zu Geolocation API</summary><ol><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/GeolocationCoordinates\"><code>GeolocationCoordinates</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/GeolocationPosition\"><code>GeolocationPosition</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/GeolocationPositionError\"><code>GeolocationPositionError</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/geolocation\"><code>Navigator.geolocation</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div id=\"sect1\"><div class=\"notecard secure\" id=\"sect2\"><p><strong>Secure context:</strong> This feature is available only in <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Security/Secure_Contexts\" class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\">secure contexts (en-US)</a> (HTTPS), in some or all <a href=\"#browser_compatibility\">supporting browsers</a>.</p></div></div>\n\n<p>The <code><strong>Geolocation</strong></code> interface represents an object able to programmatically obtain the position of the device. It gives Web content access to the location of the device. This allows a Web site or app to offer customized results based on the user's location.</p>\n\n<p>An object with this interface is obtained using the <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/geolocation\"><code>navigator.geolocation</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a> property implemented by the <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/API/Navigator\"><code>Navigator</code></a> object.</p>\n\n<div class=\"note notecard\" id=\"sect3\">\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> For security reasons, when a web page tries to access location information, the user is notified and asked to grant permission. Be aware that each browser has its own policies and methods for requesting this permission.</p>\n</div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"properties","title":"Properties","isH3":false,"content":"<p><em>The <code>Geolocation</code> interface neither implements, nor inherits any property.</em></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"methods","title":"Methods","isH3":false,"content":"<p><em><em>The <code>Geolocation</code> interface doesn't inherit any </em>method</em>.</p>\n\n<dl>\n <dt id=\"geolocation.getcurrentposition\"><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/API/Geolocation/getCurrentPosition\"><code>Geolocation.getCurrentPosition()</code></a> <span class=\"notecard inline secure\" title=\"This feature is available only in secure contexts (HTTPS)\">Secure context</span></dt>\n <dd>Determines the device's current location and gives back a <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/GeolocationPosition\"><code>GeolocationPosition</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a> object with the data.</dd>\n <dt id=\"geolocation.watchposition_en-us\"><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Geolocation/watchPosition\"><code>Geolocation.watchPosition()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a> <span class=\"notecard inline secure\" title=\"This feature is available only in secure contexts (HTTPS)\">Secure context</span></dt>\n <dd>Returns a <code>long</code> value representing the newly established callback function to be invoked whenever the device location changes.</dd>\n <dt id=\"geolocation.clearwatch_en-us\"><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Geolocation/clearWatch\"><code>Geolocation.clearWatch()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a> <span class=\"notecard inline secure\" title=\"This feature is available only in secure contexts (HTTPS)\">Secure context</span></dt>\n <dd>Removes the particular handler previously installed using <code>watchPosition()</code>.</dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"specifications","title":"Specifications","isH3":false,"content":"<table class=\"standard-table\">\n <thead>\n  <tr>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Specification</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Status</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Comment</th>\n  </tr>\n </thead>\n <tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://w3c.github.io/geolocation-api/#geolocation_interface\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" title=\"Die 'Geolocation API' Spezifikation\" rel=\" noopener\">Geolocation API</a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-rec\">Empfehlung</span></td>\n   <td>Initial specification.</td>\n  </tr>\n </tbody>\n</table>"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.Geolocation","dataURL":"/de/docs/Web/API/Geolocation/bcd.json"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p></p><p></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Geolocation_API\" title=\"/en-US/docs/WebAPI/Using_geolocation\">Using geolocation</a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Properties","id":"properties"},{"text":"Methods","id":"methods"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"},{"text":"See also","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"The Geolocation interface represents an object able to programmatically obtain the position of the device. It gives Web content access to the location of the device. This allows a Web site or app to offer customized results based on the user's location.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-07-19T02:29:32.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"Geolocation","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)"},{"title":"Geolocalización","locale":"es","native":"Español"},{"title":"Geolocation","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"Geolocation","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"Geolocation","locale":"ko","native":"한국어"},{"title":"Geolocation","locale":"pt-BR","native":"Português (do Brasil)"},{"title":"Geolocation","locale":"ru","native":"Русский"},{"title":"Geolocation","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"},{"title":"Geolocation","locale":"zh-TW","native":"正體中文 (繁體)"}],"source":{"folder":"de/web/api/geolocation","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/blob/main/files/de/web/api/geolocation/index.html","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/commit/5fe4ab11259b37914fab41914e84897fea47d143","filename":"index.html"},"parents":[{"uri":"/de/docs/Web","title":"Webtechnologien für Entwickler"},{"uri":"/de/docs/Web/API","title":"Web API Referenz"},{"uri":"/de/docs/Web/API/Geolocation","title":"Geolocation"}],"p